flowRoot.flowPara: Selecting an item from the list:
Operating system: highlights the section in the chart and shows a label.
Applications: switches to apps view (list of apps ordered by size, allows you to uninstall).
Documents, downloads, music, pictures, videos, trash: shows file list view, allows deleting files.
Cache: shows a dialog that allows clearing the cache.
If the user is an administrator, the whole disk is displayed, including space used by other users. Standard user accounts are only shown an analysis of the space they have used.
Files and directories are listed in size order.
Only one sub-folder can be expanded at once.
Colour "icons": selects and activates selection mode.
Files: opens dialog with preview (if preview is difficult, could open folder in Files with the file selected).
Secondary action shows a context menu with open, move to trash and delete actions.
Clicking a row opens the dialog for that app/component.
App network usage dialog: show amounts used by app, total used by the system, proportions, graph of usage over time. Allow limiting or turning off network access?
Cache is a hypothetical category here: could be replaced with caches and other temporary data that we know about.
